        "title": "Java recursion reverse string",
        "body": "<p>Hi I am trying understand the below recursion method but it seems too confusing. I know that the reversePrint method calls it self but my problem is,  the first time it runs it should print bcdef + a = bcdef. Here is where I get confused, the next time it runs b becomes the charAt(0)... so where is a?? Do they get stored temporally in somewhere? Can someone please help me understanding it. Many thanks<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>public static void main(String[] args) {\n    // TODO code application logic here\n    System.out.println(reversePrint(\"abcdef\"));\n}\n\npublic static String reversePrint(String s) {\n    if (s.length() &lt;= 1) {\n        return s;\n    }\n    return reversePrint(s.substring(1)) + s.charAt(0);\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
